metadata.name: Trame communale #58
metadata.description:
What does it mean to live together? What is the plan? What are we doing here? By that, I do not mean that I want to know what you are doing as an individual person, but rather what the whole of us is to achieve. Am I responsible for myself or am I responsible for you too? Am I responsible for what every single person does, or for what we collectively do as a group? Both? Neither? 

What does it mean to live together?

===

Trame communale is a generative architecture project.

The generator is made to produce 64 iterations of buildings whose structures are consistent with most plastic bricks brands.

Iterations can be virtually loaded in the anaverse under a new "village" system, which loads them all in a same space (positioned according to their order of creation).

Every owner inhabits the same commune.

metadata.name: Cold Mountain #94
metadata.description:
An impressionistic painting of a maintain on a foggy winter's day. The view will be of a mountain, mountain range, valley, or meadow. At nite, the lights come on, and the trees glow in the moonlight.

The image size is 928x1200. Press 's' to save a screenshot.

Common features:
- mountain size and stroke quality
- line quality of the trees
- 50/50 to have a spiral around the sun
- large palette with different application methods

Uncommon
- outline of the first mountain and sun
- amplified color/hue shifting

Rare
- nighttime
- no sun

metadata.name: Turbulence #343
metadata.description:
Swirly shapes are rendered by passes of poisson samples of a warped noise field. The noise shifts with each pass, creating a layered effect. 

Dense editions may take over 2 minutes to draw fully.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume at any time during the drawing.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a not 1:1 variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

Common:
- 43 set palettes plus many more with combinations
- 3 color distribution methods
- 50/50 dark
- 50/50 monochrome with bright highlights 
- 3 drawing styles: lines, points, colored pencils
- 5 noises effects: full screen, distance from center, distance from bottom, horizontal center, vertical center, random circles, 3,5, or 7 horizontal and vertical bars
- Poisson point distribution based on set layers or the noise value

Rare
- 15% chance of a dark monochrome with gold strands

metadata.name: Planetary Abstracts #281
metadata.description:
A hazy planet looms large in an alien solar system. The image is "drawn" over 1,000 iterations with colored pencils on textured paper. The final image takes about 40-50 seconds.

The image size is 1200x1200. Press 's' to save a screenshot or 'p' to pause and resume drawing.

Common features:
- 50 color palettes
- Planet size, full view to partial
- 3 to 8 moons
- 2 noise methods
- 4 color modes
- 3 focus areas (line thickness)
- Vertical or horizontal accent bars

Uncommon
- Monochrome color palette
- Mono with color highlights
- Mono with gold highlights

Rare
- Mono with dark background

metadata.name: Orchard #333
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

Copyright (c) 2022 Matt Perkins, hello@mattperkins.me, @nudoru on Twitter. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: CityScape: Istanbul #48
metadata.description:
Istanbul is a city that straddles the Bosporus Strait, and lies in both Europe and Asia, with a population of over 15 million residents. Most of the population is located in big iconic hills known as the "Seven Hills of Istanbul". 

   In this project, I tried to capture and interpret the daily life routine of the people who live in these hills with the viewing point from Bosphorus. There are three camera angle possibilities to examine the details in different layers. Also, building types, the slope of the hill, and green area density vary in between those scenarios. There are two time zones: day and night. In the night scene, there is a possibility to obtain the crescent moon which is the symbol of the culture inhabits in these lands.

To save as a high-quality image, open in live view and click yes on the incoming prompt.

Created with p5js

metadata.name: Highrise of Homes #48
metadata.description:
Highrise of Homes project is a "vertical community" to "accommodate people's conflicting desires to enjoy the cultural advantages of an urban center, without sacrificing the private home identity and garden space associated with suburbia."

Buy a cozy cottage in our steel constructed choice lots, less than a mile above Broadway, only ten minutes by elevator. All the comforts of the country with none of its disadvantages.

[Mouse Move]
- Zoomed View.

[Mouse Click]
- Focus/Unfocus to Zoomed View.

[r]
- Random Scene.

[s]
- At Main Screen: Save with 2200x2200 px.
- At Focused Screens: Save with window size.

metadata.name: Paysages Chromatiques A #106
metadata.description:
Taking my inspiration from impressionist and contemporary paintings, I tried to generate 
mixtures of more or less superimposed colors, creating flowing effects or spots as one
would obtain with paint.
This work is the first in a two-part series featuring abstraction and imagination.
I hope it will inspire you to take the time to daydream, or simply to spend a moment 
where the mind can wander freely through the colors.

To save a png file type [s]
TO remove the texture type [t]

To render at higher resolution add &pd=2 at the end of the url in live mode
(others values are valid too but be patient the rendering can be long)
---
100% code made with p5js and glsl
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.
---
Hervé (23 nov)

metadata.name: contrapuntos #676
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Rainbow Ripples Automaton #27
metadata.description:
Cells try to bounce between low and high luminance but are held by their neighbors; the hue from the highest luminance spreads to the neighbors.

'a' to stop/start the animation

metadata.name: Disturbed #107
metadata.description:
Space-time has been Disturbed. The source of the disturbance is unknown. However, sensors now indicate the presence of a Demon Overlord in the sector. Your token gives you a snapshot of the space-time perturbations at your particular location-moment of space-time. 

Your token's unique hash determines its features:

- demon overlord
- inherent vice level
- probe size  
- orientation 
- sector location

Your token's output is dimension agnostic and scales seamlessly to any screen size. 

Copyright: CC BY-NC-ND

metadata.name: Solve et Coagula #32
metadata.description:
Solve at Coagula is a generative system built entirely in p5js. The work was developed based on the abstract composition of shapes, squares and lines allowing beauty to be found within the chaos itself.

This is an original work created by Playman. 2022
